      "message": "IMO this is the wrong place to do it. We have to read it from FRAME in channel.\n\nRobot says:\n```\nmaxFrameSize is captured via handler.encoder().configuration().frameSizePolicy().maxFrameSize() inside configureHttp2(), which fires on ALPN resolution —\nbefore the peer\u0027s HTTP/2 SETTINGS preface is necessarily processed. If the peer advertises SETTINGS_MAX_FRAME_SIZE \u003e 16384, the child ChannelInitializer closure will still use the initial default (16384), missing the optimisation for that peer.\n```\n\nRead the frame size\nlazily inside initChannel() via ctx.channel().parent().pipeline().get(Http2FrameCodec.class)?",
